  "texts": [
    "An alternative ellipsoidal model, proposed by [7], starts from initially triaxial perturbations, capturing additional geometric complexity.The second step consists of applying an algorithm to identify regions in Lagrangian space where the chosen collapse model can be meaningfully applied.",
    "Over the past few decades, two primary frameworks have emerged for this task.",
    "In the so-called peak theory [e.g.",
    "21], DM halos are assumed to form around local maxima of the linearly extrapolated overdensity field, smoothed on a mass scale corresponding to the desired halo mass.",
    "The collapse model is then applied to the region surrounding the identified peak, which can be isolated using various criteria."
  ],
